cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.GR 

The paper proposes a new method for stochastic conditional image generation using basis decomposition. This is a topic that is relevant to several sub-fields of computer science, including machine learning (cs.LG), computer vision (cs.CV), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), neural networks (cs.NE), and graphics (cs.GR). Given that the paper focuses on image generation, cs.CV is a likely category, but the use of GANs and basis decomposition also suggests cs.LG and cs.AI. The paper also includes theoretical results, which could be relevant to cs.NE, and the use of graphics terminology (e.g., "multi-mode data space") suggests cs.GR as a possible category.
